<p><strong>Generation AI</strong> is a project funded by the Strategic Research Council (SRC) operating in connection with the Academy of Finland. Generation AI is one of the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.aka.fi/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus-pahkinankuoressa/ohjelmat-ja-hankkeet/shield" data-type="URL" data-id="https://www.aka.fi/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus-pahkinankuoressa/ohjelmat-ja-hankkeet/shield" target="_blank">Security and Trust in the Age of Algorithms&nbsp;(Shield) </a>programme projects. </p>



<p>The <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.aka.fi/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus-pahkinankuoressa/ohjelmat-ja-hankkeet/shield" data-type="URL" data-id="https://www.aka.fi/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus/strateginen-tutkimus-pahkinankuoressa/ohjelmat-ja-hankkeet/shield" target="_blank">Shield programme</a> focuses on security and trust in the world of information technologies and hybrid influence. In addition to more traditional security threats, both the threats and opportunities created by digitalisation and technological development, as well as various crises ranging from biodiversity loss to climate change, financial crises and geopolitical conflicts, are shaping the operating environment in unpredictable ways.&nbsp;</p>


